race.comment: RECONNAISSANCE (1) hasn't raced since the winter but has shown enough to have on top. Made debut in town before another break, then raced only once over the winter with a fast finishing second here on the all-weather. Given plenty of time and presents on the back of a trial win. Jockey has a good strike-rate for this yard and looks ideally placed for a winning return. SWEET ISSY (6) is the only other to have raced and does look a danger. Placed on debut as a juvenile then returned from a break at Belmont and was safely held in tougher company. Fitter for it and this suits. Expected to run well. PERFECT SCORE (9) is a first starter by Per Incanto out of Perfect Dream. Trial winner and with blinkers on looks ready to run well. SPECIAL COUNSEL (5) is a gelding by Star Witness making debut for the Williams yard. Fourth in a trial and must be kept safe. MADAM OUQBA (7) is a three-year-old filly by Ouqba out of Ella Jean. Senior rider on and pay to watch for a move.
